cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL 

This paper discusses a system for analyzing distributed dataflows in an online setting, which involves topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC), databases (cs.DB), software engineering (cs.SE), data structures (cs.DS), and programming languages (cs.PL). The use of Timely Dataflow and Differential Dataflow also suggests a focus on data-parallel computation and optimization, which further supports these categories.
